9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 721, L.D. 1838, “An Act to Provide
10 Opportunities and Sustainable Revenue for Maine Farms, Agricultural Fairs, Wabanaki
11 Tribes and Veterans' Homes”
12 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 39 in §1503 in subsection 2 by striking out all of
13 paragraph C (page 3, lines 21 to 23 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
14 'C. Veterans' service organizations that qualify under Section 501(c)(19) of the United
15 States Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, as a tax-exempt organization that
16 has been organized for the benefit of veterans; and'
17 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 39 in §1503 in subsection 4 by striking out all of
18 paragraph A (page 3, lines 32 to 34 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
19 'A. A licensed commercial track under subsection 2, paragraph B may operate up to
20 100 electronic wagering terminals at the location where the commercial track is
21 licensed to conduct races, subject to approval of the municipality where the commercial
22 track is licensed to conduct races.'
23 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 39 in §1503 in subsection 4 by striking out all of
24 paragraph D (page 4, lines 1 to 7 in L.D.) and inserting the following:
25 'D. A federally recognized Indian tribe under subsection 2, paragraph A may operate
26 up to 100 electronic wagering terminals on Passamaquoddy Indian territory in the case
27 of the Passamaquoddy Tribe, on Penobscot Indian territory in the case of the Penobscot
28 Nation, on Houlton Band Trust Land in the case of the Houlton Band of Maliseet
29 Indians or on Mi'kmaq Nation Trust Land in the case of the Mi'kmaq Nation. In
30 addition, a federally recognized Indian tribe may operate electronic wagering terminals
31 outside of its respective Indian territory or trust land in any municipality, subject to the
32 approval of the municipality where the electronic wagering terminals are located,
33 except that each federally recognized Indian tribe may not operate more than 100
34 electronic wagering terminals in total.'
35 Amend the bill in section 1 in c. 39 in §1503 by inserting after subsection 5 the
36 following:
