27 Amend the bill in section 1 in §1508 in subsection 1 by relettering the paragraphs to
28 read alphabetically.
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment makes the following changes to the bill.
33 1. It changes one of the persons who may be issued a license to operate electronic
34 wagering terminals from an organization eligible to conduct certain games of chance to a
35 veterans' service organization that qualifies under Section 501(c)(19) of the United States
36 Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, as a tax-exempt organization that has been
37 organized for the benefit of veterans.
38 2. It changes where a federally recognized Indian tribe may operate electronic wagering
39 terminals to specify the respective Indian territory or trust land for each tribe and to clarify
40 that a tribe may also operate electronic wagering terminals outside of its respective Indian
41 territory or trust land in any municipality, subject to the approval of that municipality.
Page 2 - 132LR1450(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 721, L.D. 1838
1 3. It provides that an electronic wagering terminal offering electronic beano may only
2 be operated by a federally recognized Indian tribe issued an electronic wagering terminal
3 license.
4 4. It clarifies that a person's being issued a license to operate electronic wagering
5 terminals is not intended to restrict that person from conducting other activities authorized
6 in law, including but not limited to pari-mutuel wagering, beano or bingo or games of
7 chance.
8 5. It provides that, when rules are initially adopted, they are major substantive rules,
9 but that any amendment or change to those rules, after initial adoption are routine technical
10 rules.
11 6. It provides that the rules required to be adopted include provisions for the internal
12 control and monitoring of the operation of electronic wagering terminals; standards for
13 minimum facility security requirements and other necessary facility requirements and for
14 staff training; and provisions governing the inclusion of problem gaming assistance
15 information in all advertising related to electronic wagering terminals.
